      "role": "user",
      "content": "I see. but if the \"reality\" is that it's been a cornerstone for a century, doesn't that basically mean the originalists are wrong? it feels like their argument is just an attempt to roll back rights that people have relied on for a long time. how do i explain to my students why one side's view seems more legally sound than the other?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
